<h2 id="open-sessions-of-board-meetings-on-15-april-and-22-july-2019">Open sessions of Board meetings on 15 April and 22 July 2019</h2>

<p>The Board, chaired by Sir Michael Rawlins, will open part of its next meetings on Monday, 15 April and Monday, 22 July to members of the public. The meeting on 15 April will run from 10:30am to 12:30pm and will take place at the Agency’s offices at 10 South Colonnade, Canary Wharf, London E14 4PU.</p>

<p>As with previous public Board meetings, the meeting will be divided into two sessions – the public session in the morning and the private session in the afternoon.</p>

<p>By necessity, discussion of matters of policy in development, commercial or staff confidentiality, certain emerging regulatory issues, forthcoming announcements or publications, will be dealt with in the private session.</p>

<p>The agenda, when finalised, along with the papers for the meeting, will be made available in electronic format on GOV.UK.  Meanwhile, a copy of the current version of the <span id="attachment_3280124" class="attachment-inline">
  <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/786385/Agenda_draft_Board_meeting_in_public_session_15_April_2019_v1.pdf">Draft Agenda meeting 15 April 2019</a>
  (<span class="type"><abbr title="Portable Document Format">PDF</abbr></span>, <span class="file-size">108KB</span>, <span class="page-length">1 page</span>)
</span>
 is attached. Also attached is the <span id="attachment_3280127" class="attachment-inline">
  <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/786386/Information_note_15_April_2019.pdf">Information note 15 April 2019</a>
  (<span class="type"><abbr title="Portable Document Format">PDF</abbr></span>, <span class="file-size">95.2KB</span>, <span class="page-length">1 page</span>)
</span>
 about the Board meeting (in public session).</p>

<p>Members of the public will have an opportunity to ask questions at the end of each discussion item at the discretion of the Chair.</p>

<p>We have space for up to ten members of the public to attend each meeting.</p>

<p>If you are interested in attending the public Board meeting on 15 April, please email by directorate directorate@mhra.gov.uk by close of Tuesday, 9 April to register.</p>

<p>Places will be allocated on a first come first serve basis. In view of the limited spaces available, it will not be possible to gain entry to the public session on the day of the meeting unless you have registered by the deadline of 9 April.</p>

<p>We plan to hold another public Board on 22 July (start time to be confirmed), with more public sessions later in the year, and notices will be published on GOV.UK nearer the time of the meetings.</p>

